description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute Medicine is seeking a dynamic Clinical Educator with a passion for all things acute care!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lancashire Teaching Hospitals Trust is one of the biggest trusts in the North West. We are the regions provider of cancer services, neurosciences, mobility and rehabilitation, renal, vascular, plastics and of course the Major Trauma Centre for the Lancashire and South Cumbria Major Trauma Network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an experienced Acute Nurse to join our acute team covering both MAU and Ambulatory care units at Preston and Chorley. This is an amazing opportunity for anyone who has a passion for acute care and wants to educate and support the nurses in this speciality. You will be expected to work with both matron’s unit mangers and the teams in each area of acute.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an extremely supportive MDT team consisting of experienced consultants, advanced nurse clinicians, experienced acute nurses, physios and health care assistants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a forward thinking team with an emphasis on staff development and training, we believe that supporting our staff to grow and develop creates a great place to work and enables us to provide excellent care with compassion. You will assist with fostering this culture and supporting our staff and service flourish.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The acute team values the personal skills, experiences and qualities that individuals bring to our department, creating a diverse and knowledgeable team who feel motivated and able to influence the future direction of our service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, if you have experience of working in acute care, a special interest in education and are keen to further your career within acute medicine then we have the job for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: TBC&lt;/p&gt;
